## Introduction
 In Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI), an Integration Instance is a fully managed, serverless platform for integrating applications and services within your OCI environment or between OCI and external systems. It enables you to build, deploy, and manage integrations using a graphical user interface (UI) and pre-built adapters.

